Using inline helpers and overloaded math functions:

```cpp
struct FVector2D {
    float X, Y;
};

// Inline directive inserts instructions directly to eliminate function call overhead
inline float Square(float Val) {
    return Val * Val;
}

// Overloaded functions have the same name but different signatures
inline float DistanceSquared(float X1, float Y1, float X2, float Y2) {
    return Square(X2 - X1) + Square(Y2 - Y1);
}

inline float DistanceSquared(FVector2D A, FVector2D B) {
    return Square(B.X - A.X) + Square(B.Y - A.Y);
}
```
